            "heading": "<strong>Bar Drains and Soda Fountains</strong>",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_HmPAx9": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><br/>Sugars from alcohol and soda syrups can quickly accumulate and block drain lines in <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/commercial-drainage-overview\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/commercial-drainage-overview\"><strong>bar drains and soda dispenser systems</strong></a>. Due to their narrow size and hidden placement, these lines are extremely difficult to clean using mechanical methods like jetting or snaking. In fact, such procedures often risk damaging the drainage system, potentially shutting down soda fountain operations. Traditional cleaning products used on bar surfaces and floors are not designed to break down sugary residue and are ineffective in clearing these types of clogs. On the other hand, harsh chemical drain cleaners may corrode pipes or push the blockage deeper into the system. As sugar buildup worsens, it emits strong, unpleasant odors—disrupting staff and leaving customers with a negative impression of cleanliness and hygiene.<br/><br/></p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
