            "heading": "<strong>Sugar Control</strong>",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_xnpU3R": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Soda fountains that mix syrup with carbonated water often face serious drain problems due to sugar buildup in the lines. With minimal water flow, the sugar solidifies into a sticky gel that leads to foul odors, persistent blockages, and infestations of <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/understanding-odors\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/understanding-odors\">drain flies</a>. These pests can carry and spread harmful bacteria, making their elimination a high priority in any hygiene-conscious environment.</p><p>Installing an <strong>EB Micro Drip or Drip System</strong> with our <strong>Sugar Eradication Bacteria</strong>, or applying <strong>Flow Fresh Gel</strong> or <strong>EBIO FOAM</strong>, allows consistent dosing of the drain lines. This effectively breaks down sugar buildup, keeps lines clear, eliminates bad smells, and removes the breeding ground for drain flies. Perfect for soda machine drains in <strong>bars, pubs, and restaurants</strong>, this solution provides a clean, cost-effective fix. Contact us to find the right program to fit your needs and budget.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
